{
    "name": "Giant Ground Cricket",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "As large as a wolf, this bulky, massive cricket has spines on its legs, back, abdomen, and head. These crickets are generally not hostile, but they protect their burrows against invasion. When agitated, a giant ground cricket secretes yellowish-green blood from its joints. This blood has a foul odor that wards off predators. Giant ground crickets stand about 2-1/2 feet tall, are approximately 5 feet long, and weigh roughly 80 pounds."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>Long spines jut from the legs and back of this enormous cricket.</i>",
